The Lagos State Environmental Protection Agency has arrested a member of the House of Representatives, Shina Peller and also sealed off his club, Quilox situated at Victoria Island, Lagos.
Peller, who is representing Iseyin/Itesiwaju/Kajola/Iwajowa Federal Constituency, Oyo State, was allegedly arrested while trying to take the bail of some clubbers arrested during the raid on the club.
The Club was sealed for noise pollution and traffic congestion. This is coming after the club organised its annual 36-hour party.
According to a statement issued by Pellerâ€™s Press Secretary, Kola Popoola, he was being detained at the Moroko Police Station, and his phone mobile seized.

			
